<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I just got the soulfire two days ago and here's some info.<BR>
1st off, you DO NOT need to be kindly with Brother Hayle in Paw.<BR>
I was high-amiable and still got the sword.  Here's the way to know<BR>
if your faction is good enough.  <BR>
Hand him the note from the banker, he will give you the note back and <BR>
state something like "I need (proof of nobility)"  You say "What proof of<BR>
nobility?) He then says "I will need the Hilt, the BSOF, your testimony, <BR>
and the note i gave back to you"<BR>
<BR>
When he says that, your faction is good to go and you can give him <BR>
the items and get your SF.<BR>
<BR>
If your faction is not good enough, go to Skel camp in SK and kill the<BR>
putrid skels.  I went from apprehensive to amiable in 2 hours.  Also go <BR>
to Qeynos and donate 2gp to Novashine.  <BR>
<BR>
When I got the soulfire the faction hit put me at kindly. <BR>
<BR>
On the level cap for the Soulfire?  A level 25 got his soulfire 2 hours<BR>
before me.  I think that is ridiculous.  It cheapens/lessens the accomplishment<BR>
of getting this sword.  At level 25, the only way to get this sword is to BEG!<BR>
<BR>
At least I actually was able to help kill Lucan and Xicotl and not have to beg for <BR>
a group of high levels to let me loot.<BR>
<BR>
Bring back the level cap to at least 35.  <BR>
<BR>
My .02<BR>
<BR>
twinkers feel free to flame me! hehe<BR>
